00:00:54,050 --> 00:00:57,510
# 还有维吉尼亚公司 #
# and the Virginia Company #

15
00:00:57,550 --> 00:01:00,180
- 准备好吊起加农炮了吗? - 好了
- Ready to hoist the cannon? - Right!

16
00:01:00,220 --> 00:01:01,780
嗨 看 那是Smith吗?
Hey, look. Is that Smith?

17
00:01:01,820 --> 00:01:03,950
就是他 没错 那个老练的水手
That's him, all right. The old sea dog.

18
00:01:03,990 --> 00:01:05,430
John Smith船长?
Captain John Smith?

19
00:01:05,460 --> 00:01:07,290
我听说过很多关于他的惊险故事
I've heard some amazing stories about him.

20
00:01:07,330 --> 00:01:09,520
你也参加这次航行吗?
Are you coming on this voyage too?

21
00:01:09,570 --> 00:01:11,530
显然 你个笨蛋!
Of course he is, you half-wit!

22
00:01:11,570 --> 00:01:13,800
没有John Smith 你别想和印第安人打交道!
You can't fight Indians without John Smith.

23
00:01:13,840 --> 00:01:15,000
没错
That's right.

24
00:01:15,040 --> 00:01:17,270
我可不想让你们这些小孩 去独享航行的乐趣
I'm not about to let you boys have all the fun.

25
00:01:18,610 --> 00:01:21,410
# 在Virginny的海岸 #
# On the beaches of Virginny #

26
00:01:21,440 --> 00:01:24,140
# 有石块大的钻石 #
# There's diamonds like debris #

27
00:01:24,180 --> 00:01:26,650
# 有银子做的河流在流淌 #
# There silver rivers flow #

28
00:01:26,680 --> 00:01:29,710
# 金子在树上采撷 #
# and gold you pick right off a tree #

29
00:01:29,750 --> 00:01:31,780
# 一块送给我亲爱的 #
# With a nugget for my Winnie #

30
00:01:31,820 --> 00:01:34,650
# 另一块留给自己 #
# And another one for me #

31
00:01:34,690 --> 00:01:36,820
# 然后剩下的全部归于 #
# And all the rest will #

32
00:01:36,860 --> 00:01:40,160
# 维吉尼亚公司 #
# go to the Virginia Company #

33
00:01:40,200 --> 00:01:42,790
# 这是荣耀 这是主 这是金子 #
# To glory, God and gold #

34
00:01:42,830 --> 00:01:49,570
# 也是维吉尼亚公司 #
# And the Virginia Company #

35
00:01:53,810 --> 00:01:55,300
抛下所有的锚!
Haul on the brace!

36
00:01:56,550 --> 00:01:58,170
加油 伙计们! 加油!
Come on, come on!

37
00:01:58,210 --> 00:02:00,180
谁 来帮帮我!
Do your best!

38
00:02:00,220 --> 00:02:01,510
当心!
Watch out!

39
00:02:05,550 --> 00:02:07,820
快点! 更多水涌进来了!
Faster! She's taking on more water!

40
00:02:11,730 --> 00:02:13,850
当心!
Look out!

41
00:02:17,230 --> 00:02:19,790
John! 快点过来!
John! Get down here!

42
00:02:19,840 --> 00:02:22,100
绑加农炮的绳断了!
The cannons are breaking loose!

43
00:02:25,810 --> 00:02:27,970
- 把帆收起来! - 是的 先生!
- Reef the topsails! - Yes, sir!

44
00:02:28,010 --> 00:02:29,570
稳住
Steady on your course.

45
00:02:29,610 --> 00:02:32,640
没事 Thomas! 我们来将它绑好
It's all right, Thomas. We'll get her tied off.

46
00:02:32,680 --> 00:02:33,980
祈祷吧 伙计们!
Say your prayers, men!

47
00:02:43,030 --> 00:02:44,890
Thomas 当心!
Thomas, watch it!

48
00:02:49,370 --> 00:02:51,490
救命!
Help!

49
00:02:51,530 --> 00:02:53,400
有人落水了!
Man overboard!

50
00:02:53,440 --> 00:02:54,600
救命!
Help!

51
00:02:54,640 --> 00:02:56,570
待在你们自己的地方! 他已经没救了!
Stay your course! He's lost!

52
00:02:56,610 --> 00:02:57,830
救命!
Help!

53
00:02:57,870 --> 00:03:00,810
- 打开钩子! - 是的 先生!
- Pull the pins! - Aye, sir!

54
00:03:04,650 --> 00:03:06,670
Smith啊!
Smith!

55
00:03:06,720 --> 00:03:08,110
Smith啊!
Smith!

56
00:03:09,520 --> 00:03:11,540
你疯了吗?
Are you crazy?

57
00:03:12,820 --> 00:03:15,090
坚持住 Thomas 我够到你了!
Hang on, Thomas! I've got you!

58
00:03:18,060 --> 00:03:19,360
快! 绳子!
Quick! The rope!

59
00:03:20,700 --> 00:03:22,660
拉!
Heave!

60
00:03:27,740 --> 00:03:29,860
加油 伙计们! 使劲拽!
Come on, lads! Pull!

61
00:03:32,410 --> 00:03:34,500
拉! 拉!
Pull! Pull!

62
00:03:34,540 --> 00:03:36,240
尽全力拉啊!
Put your back into it!

63
00:03:36,280 --> 00:03:39,180
- 拉! - 拉啊! 拉啊!
- Pull! - Pull! Pull!

64
00:03:39,220 --> 00:03:40,580
坚持住!
Hang on!

65
00:03:43,290 --> 00:03:44,780
好啦 幸运的伙计们!
There, my lucky lads!

66
00:03:46,790 --> 00:03:49,550
嗯 刚才真是爽啊
Well, that was refreshing.

67
00:03:49,590 --> 00:03:51,490
干得好 Smith
Well done, Smith.

68
00:03:51,530 --> 00:03:53,090
当然
Of course,

69
00:03:53,130 --> 00:03:54,690
要是我落水了 你们也会来救我的
you'd all do the same for me.

70
00:03:54,730 --> 00:03:56,660
- 哦 是啊 是啊 - 我们当然会的
- Oh, sure, sure. - Of course we would.

71
00:03:56,700 --> 00:03:58,000
- 当然 是啊! - 嗯 我们会的!
- Sure, yes! - Yeah, we would!

72
00:03:58,030 --> 00:03:59,860
绝对地!
Absolutely!

73
00:04:01,300 --> 00:04:03,270
甲板上出了什么麻烦吗?
Trouble on deck?

74
00:04:03,310 --> 00:04:04,600
Ratcliffe长官!
Governor Ratcliffe!

75
00:04:04,640 --> 00:04:06,270
Thomas掉进水里了 长官
Thomas fell overboard, sir.

76
00:04:06,310 --> 00:04:08,440
谢天谢地他又被救回来了
Thank heavens he's been successfully retrieved.

77
00:04:08,480 --> 00:04:10,950
- 干得好 Smith - 谢谢 长官
- Well done, Smith. - Thank you, sir.

78
00:04:10,980 --> 00:04:12,780
不要灰心 大家
Don't lose heart, men.

79
00:04:12,820 --> 00:04:15,280
离我们的新世界已经不远了...
It won't be long before we reach the New World...

80
00:04:15,320 --> 00:04:18,450
记住什么在等待着我们...
And remember what awaits us there...

81
00:04:18,490 --> 00:04:20,250
自由...
Freedom...

82
00:04:20,290 --> 00:04:21,980
繁荣...
prosperity...

83
00:04:22,020 --> 00:04:24,050
我们生命的伟大历程
the adventure of our lives.

84
00:04:24,090 --> 00:04:26,720
你们是全英国最好的船员...
You're the finest crew England has to offer...

85
00:04:26,760 --> 00:04:29,060
没有任何东西... 不论是风是雨
and nothing... not wind nor rain

86
00:04:29,100 --> 00:04:31,070
还是千百个残忍的野蛮人
nor a thousand bloodthirsty savages

87
00:04:31,100 --> 00:04:33,030
能够挡住我们的去路
shall stand in our way.

88
00:04:33,070 --> 00:04:34,430
坚持住 大家!
Carry on, men!

89
00:04:36,610 --> 00:04:38,600
一场激动人心的演说 长官
A stirring oration, sir.

90
00:04:38,640 --> 00:04:41,510
我肯定大家都很受鼓舞!
I'm sure the men were most exhilarated!

91
00:04:41,540 --> 00:04:42,840
希望是这样
Let us hope so.

92
00:04:42,880 --> 00:04:47,250
我需要那班乡巴佬去 帮我挖金子 不是吗?
I'll need those witless peasants to dig up my gold, won't I?

93
00:04:48,650 --> 00:04:51,620
新世界一定棒极了 John
This New World's gonna be great, John.

94
00:04:51,650 --> 00:04:53,950
我要去弄一大堆金子...
I'm gonna get a pile of gold...

95
00:04:53,990 --> 00:04:55,620
盖座大大的房子...
build me a big house...

96
00:04:55,660 --> 00:04:58,630
如果哪个印第安人敢阻止我 我就开枪打死他
and if any Indian tries to stop me, I'll blast him.

97
00:04:58,660 --> 00:05:01,290
你只管关心你的金子好了 Thomas
You just worry about that fortune of yours, Thomas.

98
00:05:01,330 --> 00:05:02,700
那些野蛮人交给我
Leave the savages to me.

99
00:05:02,730 --> 00:05:04,460
你觉得他们会给我们 制造很多麻烦吗?
You think they'll give us much trouble?

100
00:05:04,500 --> 00:05:07,560
Smith会给他们更多
Not as much trouble as Smith'll give them.

101
00:05:07,600 --> 00:05:09,900
# 我们会除去一个印第安人 #
# We'll kill ourselves an Injun #

102
00:05:09,940 --> 00:05:12,570
# 或者可能两个三个 #
# Or maybe two or three #

103
00:05:12,610 --> 00:05:15,100
# 我们是坚定勇敢的 #
# We're stalwart men and bold #

104
00:05:15,140 --> 00:05:18,050
# 维吉尼亚公司人 #
# of the Virginia Company #

105
00:05:18,080 --> 00:05:20,110
你们觉得新世界 将会是怎样的?
What do you suppose the New World will look like?

106
00:05:20,150 --> 00:05:21,640
就像其它的一样 我觉得
Like all the others, I suppose.

107
00:05:21,680 --> 00:05:25,250
我见过几百个新世界 Thomas
I've seen hundreds of new worlds, Thomas.

108
00:05:25,290 --> 00:05:28,420
这个会有什么区别呢?
What could possibly be different about this one?

109
00:05:28,460 --> 00:05:29,490
# 这是荣耀 这是主 这是金子 #
# It's glory, God and gold #

110
00:05:29,490 --> 00:05:30,980
# 这是荣耀 这是主 这是金子 #
# It's glory, God and gold #

111
00:05:31,030 --> 00:05:36,860
# 也是维吉尼亚公司 #
# And the Virginia Company #

112
00:06:16,240 --> 00:06:19,000
# 规律得像打鼓 #
# Steady as the beating drum #

113
00:06:19,040 --> 00:06:21,640
# 唱歌像松笛 #
# Singing to the cedar flute #

114
00:06:21,680 --> 00:06:24,010
# 四季交替 #
# Seasons go and seasons come #

115
00:06:24,050 --> 00:06:28,350
# 带来玉米 结出水果 #
# Bring the corn and bear the fruit #

116
00:06:28,380 --> 00:06:30,410
# 清甜透明的水 #
# By the waters sweet and clean #

117
00:06:30,450 --> 00:06:32,940
# 养育着有力的鲟鱼 #
# Where the mighty sturgeon lives #

118
00:06:32,990 --> 00:06:35,290
# 种下南瓜 灌溉大豆 #
# Plant the squash and reap the bean #

119
00:06:35,320 --> 00:06:39,260
# 每一寸土地都是母亲所赐 #
# All the Earth our mother gives #

120
00:06:39,290 --> 00:06:41,730
# 哦 情绪高涨 听我们唱歌 #
# Oh, great spirit, hear our song #

121
00:06:41,760 --> 00:06:44,130
# 沿袭着古老的传统 #
# Help us keep the ancient ways #

122
00:06:44,170 --> 00:06:46,570
# 维持着神圣的火焰 #
# Keep the sacred fire strong #

123
00:06:46,600 --> 00:06:50,700
# 一切都已进入我们和谐的生活 #
# Walk in balance all our days #

124
00:06:50,740 --> 00:06:52,930
# 四季交替 #
# Seasons go and seasons come #

125
00:06:52,980 --> 00:06:55,440
# 规律得就像打鼓 #
# steady as the beating drum #

126
00:06:55,480 --> 00:06:57,310
# 从李子到种子到芽再到李子 #
# Plum to seed to bud to plum #

127
00:07:02,250 --> 00:07:04,190
# 规律得像打鼓 #
# Steady as the beating drum #

128
00:07:20,900 --> 00:07:23,130
回家的感觉太好了
It's good to be home.

129
00:07:24,970 --> 00:07:27,600
Masawomecs部落被我们击败了!
The Massawomecks are defeated!

130
00:07:27,640 --> 00:07:29,610
在我们兄弟的帮助下
With the help of our brothers,

131
00:07:29,650 --> 00:07:32,240
我们的部落又安全了
our villages are safe again.

132
00:07:34,050 --> 00:07:37,680
你的回来已经为我们的部落 带来很大的愉快了
Your return has brought much joy to the village.

133
00:07:37,720 --> 00:07:41,120
看看这些笑脸
Look at all the smiling faces.

134
00:07:41,160 --> 00:07:44,460
恩 但是还有一张笑脸我没有看到
Yes, but there's one smiling face I don't see.

135
00:07:44,490 --> 00:07:46,360
我的宝贝女儿呢?
Where is my daughter?

136
00:07:46,400 --> 00:07:47,950
你知道Pocahontas
You know Pocahontas.

137
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:50,290
她有着她母亲的热情
She has her mother's spirit.

138
00:07:50,330 --> 00:07:52,960
风带她去哪儿 她就会去哪儿
She goes wherever the wind takes her.

139
00:08:11,550 --> 00:08:14,020
Pocahontas啊!
Pocahontas!

140
00:08:14,060 --> 00:08:16,420
你父亲回来了!
Your father's back!

141
00:08:16,460 --> 00:08:18,360
快下来!
Come down here!

142
00:08:18,390 --> 00:08:21,230
他回来了 Flit
He's back, Flit.

143
00:08:24,600 --> 00:08:25,790
跟上 Meeko!
Come on, Meeko!

144
00:08:33,540 --> 00:08:36,410
不! 不要走这边
No! Not that way.

145
00:08:45,490 --> 00:08:47,510
卖弄
Show-off.

146
00:09:01,470 --> 00:09:03,440
Pocahontas啊?
Pocahontas?

147
00:09:03,470 --> 00:09:07,700
Pocahontas! 你还好吗?
Pocahontas! Are you all right?

148
00:09:07,740 --> 00:09:09,230
嗯 你最好没事...
Well, you better be all right...

149
00:09:09,280 --> 00:09:11,140
因为我可不会跳下去救你!
because I'm not coming in after you!

150
00:09:14,250 --> 00:09:16,240
你不觉得我们玩这种游戏...
Don't you think we're getting a...

151
00:09:16,290 --> 00:09:18,950
年纪有点大了吗?
a little old for these games?

152
00:09:38,170 --> 00:09:40,440
帮我把船翻过来
Help me turn this thing over.

153
00:09:43,150 --> 00:09:45,050
你在那上面做什么?
What were you doing up there?

154
00:09:45,080 --> 00:09:48,280
思考 Meeko!
Thinking. Meeko!

155
00:09:48,320 --> 00:09:51,310
又是关于那个梦? 你还没有完全想出来吗?
About the dream again? Have you figured it out yet?

156
00:09:51,350 --> 00:09:52,680
我知道那一定暗示着什么东西
I know it means something.

157
00:09:52,720 --> 00:09:54,150
但就是不知道具体是什么
I just don't know what.

158
00:09:54,190 --> 00:09:56,280
你应该向你父亲问问这件事
You should ask your father about it.

159
00:09:56,330 --> 00:09:57,620
也许是该问问他
Maybe I should.

160
00:09:57,660 --> 00:09:58,960
上来 Flit
Come on, Flit.

161
00:10:00,330 --> 00:10:02,320
不要再到处乱玩 我们得回去了
Quit playing around. We have to get back.

162
00:10:06,500 --> 00:10:08,260
...面对着一个坚定的敌人
...faced a determined enemy.

163
00:10:08,300 --> 00:10:11,270
战斗从太阳刚刚升起
The battle lasted from the rising of the sun

164
00:10:11,310 --> 00:10:13,970
一直持续到夜幕降临
until the evening shadows fell.

165
00:10:14,010 --> 00:10:16,480
我们的战士勇往直前
Our warriors fought with courage,

166
00:10:16,510 --> 00:10:18,980
但是还没人像Kocoum这般勇敢...
but none as bravely as Kocoum...

167
00:10:19,010 --> 00:10:21,980
因为他战斗像熊一样的凶猛
for he attacked with the fierce strength of the bear.

168
00:10:22,020 --> 00:10:23,540
他的实际行动证明了他就是我们中最棒的...
He has proven himself to be the greatest of warriors...

169
00:10:23,590 --> 00:10:27,280
- 哦 他可真帅啊! - 我特别喜欢他的微笑
- Oh, he is so handsome! - I especially love his smile.

170
00:10:27,320 --> 00:10:29,850
消灭每一个阻挡他的敌人
Destroying every enemy in his path.

171
00:10:29,890 --> 00:10:32,520
今晚 我们要为他举行盛宴
Tonight we will feast in his honour.

172
00:10:35,900 --> 00:10:38,990
- 宝贝女儿 - 一切安好 父亲
- My daughter. - Wing-gap-o, Father.

173
00:10:39,030 --> 00:10:41,200
见到你就是我最大的快乐
Seeing you gives me great joy.

174
00:10:41,240 --> 00:10:44,030
真高兴您平安回家
I'm so glad you've come home safely.

175
00:10:44,070 --> 00:10:47,530
跟我来 我有太多话要对你说
Come with me. We have much to talk about.

176
00:10:47,580 --> 00:10:50,270
我要听听你做的每一件事情
I want to hear everything you've been doing.

177
00:10:54,780 --> 00:10:56,410
父亲 好几个晚上...
Father, for many nights now...

178
00:10:56,450 --> 00:10:58,820
我都做到同一个奇怪的梦
I've been having a very strange dream.

179
00:10:58,850 --> 00:11:01,220
我想那是要告诉我 什么事将要发生
I think it's telling me something's about to happen.

180
00:11:01,260 --> 00:11:02,620
一件激动人心的事
Something exciting.

181
00:11:02,660 --> 00:11:05,680
没错 是有一件激动人心的事即将发生
Yes, something exciting is about to happen.

182
00:11:06,860 --> 00:11:08,330
真的吗? 那是什么?
Really? What is it?

183
00:11:08,360 --> 00:11:12,030
Kocoum已经向我提亲 他要和你结婚
Kocoum has asked to seek your hand in marriage.

184
